    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.94/457</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-28T20:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1693. <persName corresp="#p_SLL1">Summers</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_BBM1">Baruch</persName>:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Your 2134, September 23, 6 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d527fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    and your 1858 [<hi rend="italic">1853</hi>], September 13, 2 p.m. Distinctly
                    understood program committees would deal only with exportable surplus. Have no
                    statistics regarding domestic stocks and will not submit any. Therefore do not
                    delay program for this information. <persName>Legge</persName>.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d527fn2">
                        <persName>Alexander Legge</persName>, Vice Chairman, War Industries
                        Board.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
